headline: Government Contractors Temper Outlooks
summary: Government contractors are having a hard time forecasting their business as the Trump administration reexamines which companies it spends its money on.  Analysts say the process of signing and renewing contracts has slowed because of Department of Government Efficiency reviews and a planned reorganization of the State Department, casting doubt on contractors’ financial futures.  The federal government was initially directing its efficiency efforts toward consulting companies such as Booz Allen Hamilton and Deloitte.
